**_Issue #3733: CI Pipeline Failures Involving the `stmgr_unittest`_**

There is an issue with running the `stmgr_unittest` on thread constrained systems. TravisCI also runs into this issue because the tier we run on provides us with 2 cores.

The initial part of this PR is supposed to test to see if the offending tests have all been isolated. On a local system with reduced cores the following tests are stuck waiting in the following busy loop:

```java
while (dummy_stmgr->NumStartBPMsgs() == 0) sleep(1);
```
In these tests:

https://github.com/apache/incubator-heron/blob/c32c09a0f09caca74dbf5715aa0632f0a50356c9/heron/stmgr/tests/cpp/server/stmgr_unittest.cpp#L1030-L1031
https://github.com/apache/incubator-heron/blob/c32c09a0f09caca74dbf5715aa0632f0a50356c9/heron/stmgr/tests/cpp/server/stmgr_unittest.cpp#L1140-L1141
https://github.com/apache/incubator-heron/blob/c32c09a0f09caca74dbf5715aa0632f0a50356c9/heron/stmgr/tests/cpp/server/stmgr_unittest.cpp#L1397-L1398

